---
// src/pages/about.astro
// The museum placard by the entrance — who made this and why.
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="A note from the person who keeps this museum."
>
  <div class="about-page">

    <!-- Decorative postmark circle -->
    <div class="about-watermark" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <article class="about-content">

      <header class="about-header">
        <span class="stamp stamp--archive">Curator's Note</span>
        <h1 class="about-title">About This Museum</h1>
      </header>

      <div class="museum-prose">

        <p>
          <em>Nyumbani</em> is a Swahili word. It means "home," but it also
          means something closer to <em>at home</em> — a state of being, not just
          a location. This museum is an attempt to build that state in a place
          where things can be kept without pressure.
        </p>

        <p>
          I built this after a long job hunt. Not as a portfolio — I already
          have one of those — but as the opposite of one. A place where nothing
          needs to perform. Where a photograph can exist because the light was
          right, not because it demonstrates a skill. Where a book reflection
          can trail off mid-thought.
        </p>

        <h2>The Rooms</h2>

        <p>
          The museum is organised into four rooms, each a different mode of
          attention:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>The Gallery</strong> — photographs, sketches, and things
            made with hands. Art does not need to be finished to live here.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>The Library</strong> — books read, passages underlined,
            thoughts that arrived while reading and needed somewhere to go.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>The Conservatory</strong> — music listened to, guitar
            practiced, the silence between notes that is also music.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>The Archive</strong> — essays. On people, on feelings, on
            the texture of living in Nairobi in your twenties.
          </li>
        </ul>
        
        <hr />

        <p class="about-closing">
          If something here reaches you — a photograph, a sentence, a chord
          progression — that is enough. You do not need to tell me.
          But if you want to, you can.
        </p>

      </div>

    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: theme('maxWidth.reading');
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5rem 2rem 6rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  /* Faint decorative circle — like a museum seal */
  .about-watermark {
    position: absolute;
    top: 3rem;
    right: -2rem;
    width: 180px;
    height: 180px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid theme('colors.vellum');
    pointer-events: none;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .about-content { position: relative; z-index: 1; }

  .about-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .about-title {
    font-family: theme('fontFamily.serif');
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: theme('colors.charcoal');
    letter-spacing: theme('letterSpacing.title');
  }

  .about-closing {
    font-style: italic;
    color: theme('colors.sepia');
  }
</style>
